---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="null hype" description="Plain Astro site for null hype.">
	<section class="hero">
		<div>
			<p class="kicker">Plain Astro</p>
			<h1>Starlight is gone.</h1>
		</div>
		<p class="lede">
			This repo is back to a normal Astro site: no docs framework, no generated
			sidebar, no starter-kit filler. Just a small static site that can grow in
			whatever direction you want next.
		</p>
		<div class="summary">
			<div class="card">
				<strong>Simple routing</strong>
				Pages now live under <code>src/pages</code> like a standard Astro project.
			</div>
			<div class="card">
				<strong>Lean dependencies</strong>
				The Starlight integration and its content wiring are removed.
			</div>
			<div class="card">
				<strong>GitHub Pages ready</strong>
				The existing Astro build flow still works with the site and base env vars.
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="section-header">
			<span class="label">What changed</span>
			<h2>Clean Astro baseline</h2>
			<p class="copy">
				The new setup keeps the repo focused on a plain static site while leaving
				your other project files and scripts alone.
			</p>
		</div>
		<div class="grid">
			<div class="card">
				<strong>Removed</strong>
				<ul class="list">
					<li>Starlight integration from <code>astro.config.mjs</code></li>
					<li><code>src/content</code> docs starter content</li>
					<li><code>src/content.config.ts</code> loader/schema plumbing</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="card">
				<strong>Added</strong>
				<ul class="list">
					<li>A standard page at <code>src/pages/index.astro</code></li>
					<li>A shared layout at <code>src/layouts/BaseLayout.astro</code></li>
					<li>Small, self-contained global styling</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
			<div class="card">
				<strong>Kept</strong>
				<ul class="list">
					<li>Astro build scripts</li>
					<li>GitHub Pages base-path compatibility</li>
					<li>Your local <code>linear-agent</code> work and scripts</li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<p class="footer">
		If you want to expand this into a fuller site, the next step is adding more
		routes under <code>src/pages</code> and moving the inline styles into a CSS
		file or component library.
	</p>
</BaseLayout>
